   Contact Us

        There are many easy ways to contact the National Women's Health
        Information Center to access thousands of publications and
        organizations with information on hundreds of health topics:

        Call Us. 1-800-994-WOMAN (1-800-994-9662) or 1-888-220-5446 for the
        hearing impaired. Trained English- and Spanish-speaking Information
        and Referral Specialists will find and order free health information
        or provide organizational referrals to assist you with any health
        questions. NWHIC's phone lines are open Monday through Friday, 9AM
        to 6PM EST (excluding federal holidays).

        Contact us electronically using our contact and customer feedback
        form. We will respond as quickly as possible to provide the best
        possible resources to answer your question. On-line resources are
        provided so you can access this information quickly. If you are
        e-mailing us about a broken link be sure to include the URL and
        title of the web page so we can find and fix it immediately.

        Write us. 8550 Arlington Blvd., Suite 300, Fairfax, VA 22031. Let us
        know what type of information you need and we will be more than
        happy to order those resources for you. Please include a return
        address, phone number, or e-mail address, so we can contact you if
        necessary.

        Newsletter:
        For current information about what's happening at the National
        Women's Health Information Center, sign up for our monthly
        newsletter listserve. Click here for subscription information.

        Please remember that NWHIC's Information and Referral Specialists
        are not trained medical specialists and therefore cannot provide
        health care advice. All questions and concerns should be directed to
        a health care provider. For more information, see our full medical
        disclaimer.

